						</paratext>
						<eop/>
					</para>
					<para>
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<paratext>See also <cite.query w-src-number="0287017178" w-serial-number="1982103530" w-seq-number="00015" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000711" ID="I0548f3d274d311eab2f0b920da2605c5">Myers v. State, 160 Ga. App. 685, 288 S.E.2d 27 (1981)</cite.query>, which held that in a rape case, former O.C.G.A. § 24-3-4 [§ 24-8-803(4) eff. Jan. 1, 2013] must give way to former O.C.G.A. § 24-2-3 [§ 24-4-412 eff. Jan. 1, 2013]; thus, statements as to earlier intercourse made to a doctor were not admissible.<eos/>
